results.name: Least difference of primes p, q such that p < n^3 < q.
comment: There are numbers k other than 2 such that a(k) = 4. The first few (up to 1000) are 129 189 369 435 549 555 561 819. Conjecture: every even integer greater than 2 occurs infinitely often in this sequence. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, May 13 2016
link: Zak Seidov, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 21 2002
